From a3eca26ce187d66e201434048887d3ff7b926f5d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miroslav Zagorac <mzagorac@haproxy.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 07:25:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Exposed SetBackgroundWaitFor() through OTLP/HTTP
 exporters

Added a virtual SetBackgroundWaitFor() method to the base HttpClient
interface, allowing the curl background thread idle timeout to be
configured from the exporter level.  The method propagates through
OtlpHttpClient and the three OTLP HTTP exporters (traces, metrics,
logs) down to the underlying curl::HttpClient.  Made the existing
curl::HttpClient SetBackgroundWaitFor() a noexcept override of the
new base class method.

Fixed an integer overflow in the background thread idle-wait comparison:
when background_thread_wait_for_ was set to milliseconds::max(), the
comparison against the elapsed system_clock::duration caused an implicit
conversion to nanoseconds, overflowing int64_t and making the thread exit
immediately after starting.
